HEADWORD: Reforge
<hw>Re*forge"</hw> <pr>(r?*f?rj")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>re-</ets> + <ets>forge</ets>: cf. F. <ets>reforger</ets>.]</ety>
<def>To forge again or anew; hence, to fashion or fabricate anew; to
make over.</def> <rj><au>Udall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reforger</ent>⟦br⟧
